title: Epica Double Wide UV Curing Nail Dryer for Acrylic Gel/Shellac Manicures 54 Watt
description: You've seen the fabulous new gel/shellac manicures on celebs, now give yourself that perfectly polished, professional-quality look at home. The Epica makes it foolproof by putting all the functionality, convenience and safety features that professionals enjoy at your fingertips.Double Wide Lamp BayMeasuring a generous 11.5"W x 5"D, the drying area gives you plenty of room to insert two hands or feet without crowding or smudging...and cuts your drying time in half. The bay's interior is mirrored to ensure full, even UV light distribution, without hot spots.Convenient Front Controls with 3 Operating ModesDesigned especially for the home user, the Epica's control panel is on the front for easy access, while manicurist industry models put the controls on the back. In UV mode, its 6 ultraviolet bulbs output 54 total watts of gel polish curing light. For air drying conventional polishes, 2 fans provide a constant, circulating air flow to reduce wait time. You can also run the UV light and fans at once for the ultimate in fast, comfortable nail drying.Safety Timer with Auto Shut-offChoose from 6 preset drying session lengths: 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 and 7 minutes. At the end of the session the alarm will sound and the Epica will automatically shut off to prevent accidental UV overdoses.Easy and Safe to UseThe Epica is designed for maximum operating convenience with soft-touch controls and easy-to-read LED displays. It is also fuse protected, and has received CE testing and certification that it meets international standards of safety. It comes with 6 UV bulbs, plus 1 extra replacement bulb.
